One of the first people in the industry to ever believe in us was Ken Block. The first time I was ever brought out to LA to do a job was Gymkhana and that was an incredibly surreal experience. We came down twice and spent the days with Ken Block and crew. I can not express to you all how incredible this guy was. He spent every free moment on set passing along wisdom and advice to us. He was such an incredible resource, mentor and all around awesome person.
I’m very sad to hear of his passing and we are sending his family and friends healing hugs and comforting prayers.

FIGHT WEEK! New doc following @harleyplays journey up to fight week is now live on EMT. Link in bio for the full video.

“What a thrill”
 I began boxing a year and a half ago to train for Creator Clash. We raised 1.3m$ for charity at CC1 and looks like that’s happening this year again for Creator Clash 2. 
Thank you to my coach @coachthompsonboxing for giving me the tools I needed in the ring. I may not have won but I’m walking away without a single scratch on me. My biggest concern was defending myself and even though I took some hits, I felt confident and prepared. I had some more rounds in me.
Thank you @luimarco for guiding me to getting in the best shape of my life. I’ve never been stronger and healthier than I am now. 
Shout out to @johnhennigan for making me feel alive again! I’ll see you in a ring again one of these days. Any ring will do. 
Thank you @idubbbz for letting me take part in this and thank you @anisajomha for literally making this whole event happen! You guys really made it next level this time around. 
Thank you to everyone that helped me, there are too many to name here, but you know who you are. If you’ve helped me on my boxing journey to becoming who I am today, I appreciate you for that and I am grateful. 

That was fun!! I think I got another fight in me. Can’t stop on a loss 😏

I was a fanboy all weekend at Creator Clash. Got to see some of my favorites!! What a good time. 
  Also, this is me the day after my fight. Totally fine, no injuries. Kind of annoying tbh
